## 2026-03-27 - Keyboard shortcuts modal uses Mac-only symbols (⌘, ⇧) with no legend or platform-adaptive labels for non-Mac users
- Added platform detection utilities (`isMac`, `modKey`, `shiftKey`, `adaptShortcut`) to `shared/utils.ts`. `adaptShortcut` replaces ⌘→Ctrl+ and ⇧→Shift+ on non-Mac platforms, leaving Mac unchanged.
- Updated `KeyboardShortcutsModal.tsx` to call `adaptShortcut(key)` at render time so all shortcut labels adapt per platform.
- Updated all other files with hardcoded Mac symbols: `App.tsx` (command palette trigger, paste menu item, command entry shortcut), `EmptyState.tsx` (⌘N hint), `PasteTokensModal.tsx` (⌘↵ tooltip), `SelectionInspector.tsx` (⌘⇧D tooltip).

